msDesc.head: Martyrology of Usuard, Adapted for the Use of Strängnäs Diocese

supportDesc.foliation: paginated 1-11 in dark brown ink by a modern hand, foliated 7-124 in pencil by a modern hand.

collation.p: VisColl collation. Two folios at the end, , should be placed before .
collation.catchwords: Catchwords visible on quires 2-10; 13; 15, some partially lost due to trimming.

p.note: Top of page, in pencil by a modern hand: A:28 (current signum). In brown ink by a modern hand: 21 B. In brown ink by a medieval hand: prima secunde. In brown ink by two early modern hands: Martyrologia Sive descriptio Brevis omnium Martyrum Singulis Anni Diebus adscriptum Ecclesiae olim Stregnensis. National Library book label with current signum in black ink. Bottom of page, in brown ink by an early modern hand: N:9 (unidentified signum).
Musical notation, of unknown date, in black ink.

binding.p: Medieval binding. Dark brown skin over wooden boards. 4 double raised bands and 2 endbands. On , stamped in gold: A 28 (current signum). Remnants of a clasp on , marks of a clasp on . The straps are missing.
binding.condition: The volume has been repaired; the spine is modern.

provenance.p:
According to Paulsson
, the volume was first used at Strängnäs cathedral ca . It was still in use there in , as shown by an annotation on .
The Antiquities Archive. The current signum, A 28, was first established in Helin’s catalogue from the 1720s (U 91:2:2).

acquisition.p: From the Antiquities Archive to the Royal Library in .

note.p: Important events are noted by various late medieval scribes, for example:
: Anno milleno cd scilicet l que secundo portauit varia dampna satis skania (memorial verse about Karl Knutsson's campaign in Scania )

: Anno domini mcdlxxiii combusta est ecclesia Strengnensis cum campanis organis et quibusdam ymaginibus una cum claustro ordinis predicatorum capella sancti Eskilli magna multitudine populi et tota ciuitate duodecim curiis prelatorum et canonicorum exeptis casuali incendio circa meridiem Sabato Dominice Trinitatis

: Anno domini mdprimo obiit venerabili in christo pater dominus Conradus rogge Episcopus Strengenensis decretorum doctor Qui ecclesiam ipsam pro magna parte ex vtrique parte amplicare fecit choro et prebenda sancti erici decorauit Summum altare cum tabula regula mitra baculo pastorali et antependiis precioribus perornauit

: Anno domini mdxxxvo In crastino iohannis ante portam Latinam Sexta feria infra octavam ascensionis domini hora 3a post prandium Combusta est tota ciuitas Strengenensis casuali incendio cum capellis Demptis dumtaxat Ecclesia cathedrali monasterio predicatorum Sola domo lapidea domini Episcopi non tamen sine grandi dampno et periculo cum nonnullis curiis ruinosis et paucis domibus in parte occidentali omittatis deo auxiliante

note.p:
The Martyrology has been adapted for the use of Strängnäs diocese. The solemnities of certain feast days have been changed or added, see further Schmid (1932)
. Additional feast days, such as Scandinavian saints, as well as notable anniversaries and events have been added in the margins, for example:
: Eodem die beati henrici episcopi et martiris festum duplex; Eodem die anniuersarium domini ingeualdi quondam prepositi strengnesis
: Eodem die Anniuersarium domini thome quondam episcopi Strengensis
: Eodem die sancti Sighfridi episcopi et confessoris festum totum duplex
: Eodem die Anniuersarium Domini Magni andree quondam Canonici Strengensis
: Eodem die Anniuersarium domini Thome quondam Episcopi Strengenesis
: Eodem die Anniuersarium domini Erici Kagga Prepositi Strengenensis
: Eodem die Anniuersarium domini Nicolai Magni prebendati Strengenesis; Eodem die Beati Erici martiris quodam illustrissimi regis Swecie Totum duplex (with drawing)
: Anno domini 1532 Incepta est Missa primalis swecana in ecclesia Stregenensi feria quinta pentecostes
: Anniuersarium domini Ingeualli prebendati Strengensis
: Eodem die sancte elene martyris vesgocie festum duplex
: Dominica proxima post lamberti habeatur anniuersarium Reuerendi in chrsto patris domini Conradi Episcopi alme ecclesie Strengnensis.

According to Wiktorsson (2015)
, this and some other notes are written by Nils Petersson Bang, canon in Strängnäs 1493–1542.
: Eodem translacio sancti eskilli episcopi martiris festum duplex
: Eodem die beate Birgitta patrone Swecie festum duplex
: Item Octaue sancti Eskilli episcopi et martiris festum duplex

supportDesc.condition: Several pages are stained and dirty. Several holes throughout the volume. Certain feasts have been erased or changed, for example on and . Smudge on . Five stubs from a medieval breviary (or similar) have been inserted in the last quire, probably as support for the damaged binding. badly damaged; half of the page missing.

handDesc.handNote: ) may be written by another hand.

p.note: Bottom of page, in brown ink by a contemporary cursive hand: a text in Old Swedish about the purchase of Scania, beginning: Skanø var køpt til Swerge. A similar text is also recorded in Linköpings stifts- och landsbibliotek, MS J 77, fols 141r-142r.
In the left margin, in black ink by a medieval hand, partially erased: drawing of St Erik with royal crown.
Fragment of a theological text (breviary?), with quotes from the Bible and St Augustine.

Top of page, in dark brown ink by a contemporary hand: Tu in nobis es domine et nomen sanctum tuum atque gloriosum inuocatum est super nos ne derelinquas nos domine deus noster deo gracias (Jeremias 14:9). After this, in light brown ink by a contemporary hand: prayer, partially lost since half of the page is missing, beginning Et ne nos inducas in temptacionem.
Musical notation (square notation, four staves) and illegible notes.

decoDesc.p: Main text in brown ink. Rubrics in red. Capitals touched in red. Paragraph signs in red and blue.

decoNote.p: : Top of the pages: plain initial KL in blue and red over ca 5 lines, with flourishing in contrasting colours. : Puzzle initial C in red and blue over 6 lines. : Plain initials over 1-3 lines in red, blue and green with flourishing, sometimes in the form of flowers, in the margins.
